trans-unit.source: Mobile Services integrates with Azure Notification Hubs to support additional push notification functionality, such as templates, multiple platforms, and improved scale.

trans-unit.source: The global <languageKeyword>push</languageKeyword> object is used to register for push notifications with Notification Hubs and send messages to template registrations.
trans-unit.target: The global <languageKeyword>push</languageKeyword> object is used to register for push notifications with Notification Hubs and send messages to template registrations.

trans-unit.source: Use the platform-specific push objects to send messages to native registrations.
trans-unit.target: Use the platform-specific push objects to send messages to native registrations.

trans-unit.source: While you can register for push notification from your Mobile Services backend, we recommend that you have the client register for notifications by calling registration methods on the client.
trans-unit.target: While you can register for push notification from your Mobile Services backend, we recommend that you have the client register for notifications by calling registration methods on the client.
